# Path Alias Imports

Prefer `@` path alias for imports (e.g. `@app`, `@shared`, `@core`) instead of relative paths.

## Examples

```typescript
// ❌ Avoid
import { WorkOrderService } from '../../../core/services/work-order.service';

// ✅ Prefer
import { WorkOrderService } from '@app/core/services/work-order.service';
```

## When to Use

- Importing from modules, services, or shared code
- Avoid relative paths like `../../../` when an alias is available
